(6,7,'2009-10-21 18:11:36','2009-10-21 16:11:36','The Raw Shaping Form Finding research project started in 2004 with a technology scan on experts and students Industrial Design and Engineering Design at the University of Twente in the Netherlands. The questions asked were about futures, possibilities, implications and use of emerging technologies for shaping and form giving tools in a virtual- or augmented reality environment. After this technology-scan we started implementing specific design experiments and assignments in the Design Education Program at the University of Twente. In the last five years we gathered and captured lots of design data and tangible results of student work from our experiments, methods and assigned tasks. After analyzing and evaluating the Raw Data, these Data Sets became the foundation for our [re]search and experimentation endeavour.\r\n\r\nIn January 2009 we continued our in-depth research with the launch of RSFF (Raw Shaping Form Finding) and the Seven Haptic Representational Experiments we set-up in our laboratory. Thus far, we tested 83 experts and novice designers in over two-hundred individual experiments. We expect to come out with preliminary results by the end of 2009. During the ICSID Design Education Conference 2009 in Singapore we showed our first preliminary results of our findings and discoveries. We showed a prototype hybrid tool based on two-handed tangible  interaction in conjunction with a Virtual Design Assistant.\r\n\r\nEarly 2010 we started a new series of experiments based on tacit and tangible interaction design during which we are testing participants blindfolded and immerse them in creating tangible artifacts.  By the end of 2010 we expect to  introduce our first prototype of our RSFF tools, an intuitive  shaping and form giving workbench with the immersive experience of  augmented reality.\r\n\r\nCurrently we are engaged in prototyping, testing and programming software to support the Virtual Design Assistant workbench-system. Please feel free to contact us for more information.\r\n\r\nEnjoy the website and content.\r\n\r\nThe Raw Shaping Society © 2009','About','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2013-04-03 13:35:29','2013-04-03 13:35:29','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.nl/?p=6',0,'post','',0),
