(60,7,'2009-11-19 19:02:48','2009-11-19 17:02:48','We scratch, construct and manipulate the earth resources with our tools and artifacts, making buildings, fabricate structures, thereby creating and producing our manifestations of thinking, dreaming and tinkering. We are leaving marks, traces, roaming about and searching for beauty and nature often without real preset goals or destinations.\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05052011410-450x253.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05052011428-450x253.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05052011431-450x253.jpg\" />\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/RAW_Shaping_DSTestCase4-450x274\" />\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/RAW_Shaping_DSTestCase3-450x337.jpg\" />\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/P5250143-450x337.jpg\" />','Raw Shapes','','publish','open','open','','raw-shapes','','','2009-11-19 19:02:48','2009-11-19 17:02:48','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=60',0,'post','',0),
(62,7,'2009-11-19 19:09:42','2009-11-19 17:09:42','We need to Rethink - Readapt - Remake our Computational Design Tools, bringing back the intuitive, tacit and tangible into our World of Ideas. RSFF nudges towards hybrid design tools and engaging designers in two-handed interaction to increase control, stimulate manual dexterity and bringing out intuitive interactions.','Tools','','publish','open','open','','tools','','','2009-11-19 19:09:42','2009-11-19 17:09:42','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=62',0,'post','',0),
(66,7,'2009-11-19 19:19:50','2009-11-19 17:19:50','The Designer shows activity, the Designer is processing, the Designer is making use of Representations. The Designer is sharing  ideas or  fuzzy-notions in some form or way, exploring and shaping tangible artifacts that will be manifest to the world. The Designer uses sensory perceptions and sensory feelings by way of distributed cognition during design processing.\n\nThe Designer has lots of intent...Raw Shaping inspires to bring out  the unintentional, the improbable and enhances serendipity.','The Designer [homunculus intentio]','','publish','open','open','','the-designer-homunculus-intentio','','','2009-11-19 19:19:50','2009-11-19 17:19:50','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=66',0,'post','',0),
