(100,7,'2009-11-25 02:44:15','2009-11-25 00:44:15','If you are looking for partnership, collaboration, untethered interaction design or project cooperation, our RSFF Design Group is more than able to work with you!\n\nCommunicate and share with us your perpetually changing wishes and trajectories to create new and stronger links between design, meaning and production.  We need to bring back design and production to a new level of basic cooperation, implementation of integrated global care, identifying blind-spots, negotiating with stakeholders, being pro-active, understanding of variable context and bringing back the traditional skills to industry and production.','RSFF will handle your projects','','publish','open','open','','rsff-will-handle-your-projects','','','2009-11-25 02:44:15','2009-11-25 00:44:15','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=100',0,'post','',0),
(106,7,'2009-11-28 23:18:53','2009-11-28 21:18:53','After presenting the paper: \'\'Bridging the Design Gap: Towards an Intuitive Design Tool\' there were numerous people who reacted very positive to our [re]search topics and findings. It was a good feeling to know that Intuitive Tangible Design is not yet forgotten and still has merit and powerful potential as a design tool. Keynote speaker Satoshi Nakagawa who himself talked about \'The Right Brain Smile\' findings based upon and derived from KANSEI methodology, said afterwards that he was intrigued by Raw Shaping Form Finding.The results shown, exhibiting experiments designers were engaged in and the hybridization of two-handed interaction and computational design were close or overlapping his views, findings and research results. Plans of further cooperation were discussed and will be developed in due time.','After Singapore...','','publish','open','open','','after-singapore','','','2009-11-28 23:18:53','2009-11-28 21:18:53','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=106',0,'post','',0),
(147,7,'2010-02-03 19:53:27','2010-02-03 17:53:27','We started new experimentations in January 2010 for RSFF.  Presently we focus our experimentation on tangible form finding through manipulations in plastically formable mass. We immersed 82 industrial design engineering students in tangible design activities wearing blindfolds. The idea behind being blindfolded has been explored in the past by other research groups in the domain of architecture and design. However, we apply some new tangible aspects and tacit parameters to this method to allow the raw shaping and finding of form to manifest itself. Students are not allowed to see the results during or after the experimentation process. During the experimentation we use several video cameras to capture the processing and results.\n\nAll our research is based on random tinkering and testing, never knowing where we are going with it, it is all based on serendipity, surprise, spontaneity, lucky circumstances and just hard work. Thanks to Louis Pasteur!','RSFF Blindfolded ','','publish','open','open','','rsff-blindfolded','','','2010-02-03 19:53:27','2010-02-03 17:53:27','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=147',0,'post','',0),
(156,7,'2010-02-17 12:29:52','2010-02-17 10:29:52','On March 16th, 2010 we made some tests with the FARO LS Photon in our [re]search lab at he University of Twente, we\'d like to thank FARO Benelux BV for their time and demonstration of the scanner. We explored the various possibilities and features of the Photon scanner and software. Shown are some of the results of this session. For more information: <a href=\"http://www.faro.com/holland.aspx?elq=nl&amp;elq=01e040f840e24025b1a218234676e525\">www.faro.com</a>\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro01.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro02.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro03.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro04.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro05.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro06.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/faro07.jpg\" />','FARO Demo Day at RSFF Lab','','publish','open','open','','image-post','','','2010-02-17 12:29:52','2010-02-17 10:29:52','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=156',0,'post','',0),
(189,7,'2010-03-01 13:51:58','2010-03-01 11:51:58','Once again we are selected to present our [re]search on Raw Shaping Form Finding during the VRIC2010 (Virtual Reality International Conference) in Laval (Paris) in April.\n\nOn April 7th at 09:10 AM  there will be a teaser presentation on \'Exploring Tacit and Tangible Interaction Design: Towards an Intuitive Product Design Tool\'. Later on that morning there will be a Symposium 1 with poster presentation on Virtual and Augmented Reality for Product Design.\n\nTo get in the mood, listen to \"April in Paris\" by Vernon Duke and Yip Harburg! (Various recordings: Count Basie, Bill Evans, Thelonious Monk, Ella Fitzgerald etc.)\n\nFollow this link for the program:\n\n<a title=\"rawshaping\" href=\"http://www.laval-virtual.org/#VRIC 2010-Symposium 1 :&lt;br&gt;Virtual and Augmented Reality for Product Design\">http://www.laval-virtual.org/#VRIC 2010-Symposium 1 :&lt;br&gt;Virtual and Augmented Reality for Product Design</a>\n\nEnjoy!','April in Paris! 2010','','publish','open','open','','rsff-april-in-paris','','','2010-03-01 13:51:58','2010-03-01 11:51:58','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=189',0,'post','',0),
(261,7,'2010-03-22 16:20:36','2010-03-22 14:20:36','On March 17th, 2010 the RSFF [re]search group visited Landre Werkmetaal in Vianen for a demonstration of multi-layered manufacturing using the V-Flash 3D printing technology. We sent a STL file of a raw shaped Virtual Clay model to Landre the night before to witness the results the next day at their location in Vianen. The V-Flash gave some good results and especially the speed and affordability are interesting aspects of instant prototyping during RSFF. Shown are some of the raw virtual models and results of the 3d raw models during and after printing. Further included are some other examples of rapid prototyping made with the V-Flash and Projet 3000 3D printers. We\'d like to thank Landre Werkmetaal BV for their support and demos. For more information: <a title=\"blocked::http://www.landre-werkmetaal.com/\" href=\"http://www.landre-werkmetaal.com/\">www.landre-werkmetaal.com</a>\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/RAW_Shaping_DSTestCase4.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/autootje.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/autootje_mesh3_logo.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre01.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre03.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre7.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre29.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre31.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre37x.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre35.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre19.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre04.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre10.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre12.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Landre23.jpg\" />','Demo Day at Landre Werkmetaal BV','','publish','open','open','','demo-day-at-landre-werkmetaal-bv','','','2010-03-22 16:20:36','2010-03-22 14:20:36','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=261',0,'post','',0),
(268,7,'2010-03-22 16:35:18','2010-03-22 14:35:18','RSFF is aiming at the identification of essential voids in the support of design processes offered by commonly available methods and tools. Some remarkable results were obtained during design sessions with novices and experts by engaging them in tangible experiments that were designed to stimulate and enhance their skills, tacit knowing and creativity that enable them to represent their ideas and concepts in an intuitive way. We explored and captured the differences in designer\'s behavior during use of \"analogue\" and digital representation tools. This approach leads us in the direction of creating an exciting hybrid design tool to bring the tacit and tangible elements of design back into CAD systems. \n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/chart-xd.jpg\" />\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/RSFF%20schema%20sequences.png]\n','RSFF Framework','','publish','open','open','','rsff-framework','','','2010-03-22 16:35:18','2010-03-22 14:35:18','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=268',0,'post','',0),
(271,7,'2010-03-22 16:40:18','2010-03-22 14:40:18','Some remarkable results were obtained during design sessions with novices and experts by engaging them in tangible experiments that were designed to stimulate and enhance their skills, tacit knowing and creativity that enables them to represent their ideas and concepts in an intuitive way.\nWe explored and captured the differences in designers\' behaviour during use of \"analogue\" and digital representation tools. In laboratory experiments we embedded a set of observations to measure the effectiveness,various shaping and representation techniques. Knowledge about learning curves, time constraints, idiosyncrasy, quality of design results and focus of particular design methods gives insight in peoples abilities to improve and support decisions about the structure and content of the \"best\" curriculum for industrial design engineering students. For the experiments, we used nine (9) haptic representational configurations and set-ups, and involved over 95 participants per experiment. In these configurations the participant\'s performance of form giving and shaping techniques were captured, observed and rated.\n\nNine (9) haptic test benches for three-dimensional design representations:\n1: Pencil Sketch test bench  [vimeo 10381990]\n2: Sand Sketch test bench [vimeo 10382551]\n3: Sculpting test bench [vimeo 10351035]\n4: Wire Plying test bench [vimeo 10382683]\n5: Steam Sketching test bench [vimeo 10350603]\n6: Solid Works test bench [vimeo 10351195]\n7: Virtual Clay test bench [vimeo 10351524]\n8: Blindfold Tacit test bench\n9: Blindfold Tangible test bench\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/9-experim%20RSFF%20nr%20crop.jpg\" />','RSFF Nine [9] Experiments','','publish','open','open','','rsff-nine-9-experiments','','','2010-03-22 16:40:18','2010-03-22 14:40:18','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=271',0,'post','',0),
(291,7,'2010-03-23 14:10:33','2010-03-23 12:10:33','[I\'ve read the news today...oh boy...no news from this front.]\r\n\r\nMay 2011\r\n\r\nWe launched the LFDS hybrid design tool in Design Education. We immersed over ninety (90)  students in design interaction in conjunction with the LFDS. They were grouped in pairs to accomplish a specific design task. Apart from the keeness, curiosity and enjoyment the students made hundreds of speedy iterations and instances. We will post some of the results at later date this site.\r\n\r\nMay 2011\r\n\r\nRobert will present his paper about Novel Approach in Custom Value Engineering during the WINVR2011 Conference in Milan, Italy end of June. We\'ll keep you notified.\r\n\r\nApril 2011\r\n\r\nLaval Virtual 2011 was superb, we demoed the LFDS for three days during the Pro-Exhibition resulting in great response and enthusiasm of the visitors. Robert presented his paper during the  VRIC2011 about Cognition, Intuition and Interaction Design. All in all great experience, great time and harmonious work.\r\n\r\nFebruary 2011\r\n\r\nOur contribution to VRIC2011, Virtual Laval in France, has been accepted! We will keep you posted.\r\n\r\nJanuary 2011\r\n\r\nOur Video contribution on LFDS  to the IEEE VR2011 Conference in Singapore has been accepted!  Instead of writing another paper on the Hybrid Design Tool we decided to present a video on our [re]search endeavors and experimentations. Good start of the new year...! Nice going!\r\n\r\nDecember 2010\r\n\r\nRSFF is working\r\n\r\nNovember 5th, 2010\r\n\r\nWe did a Value Engineering session at ProRail in Utrecht with our LFDS Design Tool, impressive and exciting event with a variety in stakeholders working on a real life Project Alkmaar. This next generation of Railway stations 2015  will incorporate new visions on traffic flows of  passengers, commercial areas and infra-structural traffic systems.\r\n\r\nFor more information see the post on the home page.\r\n\r\nSeptember 27th - October 1st, 2010\r\n\r\nDuring the JVRC 2010 (Joint Virtual Reality Conference) in Stuttgart, Robert E. Wendrich will  be presenting and demonstrating a prototype of the LFDS [Loosely Fitted Design Synthesizer]. He will also present first results of working with the LFDS in a real world case-based scenario for ProRail [Dutch National Railway] in the Netherlands.\r\n\r\nFollow this link for more information: <a href=\"http://www.jvrc2010.org/\">http://www.jvrc2010.org/</a>\r\n\r\nMay 20th, 2010\r\n\r\nWell it is a fact, RSFF has been published in a International CAD Journal! Computer-Aided Design and Applications (ISSN 1686-4360) is an independent, international peer-reviewed technical journal dedicated to the applications of computer-aided design and manufacturing. This special issue is titled CAD in the Arts and RSFF is part of it!\r\n\r\n[pdf CADandA_7_4_505-531.pdf]\r\n\r\nMay 4th, 2010\r\n\r\nRobert E. Wendrich will be presenting \'RSFF: Exploring Intuitive Design through Tangible Real &amp; Virtual Real\'  during the Conference of Bridges: Mathematical Connections in Art, Music and Science. The conference will take place in Pécs, Hungary, during July 24 - 29, 2010.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bridgesmathart.org/bridges-2010/\">http://bridgesmathart.org/bridges-2010/</a>\r\n\r\nApril 13th, 2010\r\n\r\nRobert E. Wendrich will be Keynote at the ASME 2010 World Conference on Innovative Virtual Reality (WINVR2010) in Ames, Iowa, USA on May 12-14th to speak about RSFF: Hybrid Design Tool.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.asmeconferences.org/WINVR2010/\">http://www.asmeconferences.org/WINVR2010/</a>\r\n\r\nApril 9th, 2010\r\n\r\nRobert E. Wendrich will be presenting during the EuroVR conference in Paris  on May 6 - 7th speaking on RSFF: Hybrid Design Tool and [re]search challenges in VR/AR technologies for design activities.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eurovr-eve-2010.limsi.fr\">http://eurovr-eve-2010.limsi.fr</a>\r\n\r\nApril 8th, 2010\r\n\r\nRSFF WINNER of the VIRTUAL LAVAL AWARD 2010\r\