(698,7,'2011-03-18 21:01:59','2011-03-18 19:01:59','This year we will show our Loosely Fitted Design Synthesizer [LFDS] during the IEEE Virtual Reality Conference in Singapore. Our contributions to this event focus on individual and collaborative interaction within mixed reality, thereby assisted by our hybrid design tool; a video contribution is prominently shown at the venue during the course of the conference.\n\nWe present a working prototype of a Hybrid Design Tool to support collaborative interaction during design ideation, value engineering and conceptualization. In this mixed-reality environment we support tangible interaction with real-world objects, artifacts and materials through two-handed interaction and manipulation. Simultaneously the iterative sequences are real-time video captures and are visualized virtually on screen. The loosely-fitted architecture supports speedy interaction, choice-architecture, decision-making and intuitive representation.  The iterative instances are stored and listed while the system affords and assists the user to synthesize these iterations. Tangible representation in conjunction with virtual representation supports the distributed cognitive resonance and triggers the creativity, evokes inspiration and releases interactive flow. The mixed-reality environment gives the user a semi-immersive experience during the interaction. The creation of a special workbench, horizontally or vertical, re-enacts the craftsmanship and bestows meaning on physical design or engineering activity. Thinking-on-your-feet will have a direct influence on knowing-in-action. Cognitive response from sensorial input stimulates the mind, provokes thought processes and is instrumental to manipulative actions and gestures. The horizontal workspace allows physical interaction, whereas the vertical workspace represents the virtual realm. The Hybrid Design Tool is a metaphorical approach to bridge the real and virtual worlds placing the human-in-the-loop during interaction and collaborative simulation.\n\n[vimeo 20834727]\n\nFor more information:<a href=\" http://conferences.computer.org/vr/2011/ \"> http://conferences.computer.org/vr/2011/ </a>','LFDS at IEEE Virtual Reality 2011 in Singapore','','publish','open','open','','lfds-at-ieee-virtual-reality-2011-in-singapore','','','2011-03-18 21:01:59','2011-03-18 19:01:59','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=698',0,'post','',0),
