(759,7,'2011-05-26 14:47:33','2011-05-26 12:47:33','On Tuesday May 24th, 2011 the Raw Shaping Society launched their hybrid design tool LFDS [Loosely Fitted Design Synthesizer] in Design Education context. Over ninety (90) Bachelor students in Industrial Design at the University of Twente were immersed in design ideation and creative exploration in conjunction with the hybrid tools. The students were asked to group randomly in Design Pairs. The Design Pairs were given an assignment to design a vehicle or automotive object. The paired collaborative session lasted for five (5) minutes, to make speedy iterations with tangible materials. We offered two complete horizontal LFDS workbenches and systems for the design sessions. Each LFDS Workbench had one moderator to assist in case of dire need. Furthermore the students were given a set of two dimensional \'wheels\' to trigger their initial ideas. Results of the student sessions will be posted at later date.\r\n\r\nFor some videos:\r\n\r\n[vimeo 24266658] [vimeo 24275139] [vimeo 24279573]\r\n\r\nFor pictures:\r\n\r\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu01.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu02.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu04.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu05.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu06.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu08.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu09.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/LFDS%20Edu13.jpg\" />','RSFF Launches LFDS in Design Education 2011','','publish','open','open','','rsff-launched-lfds-in-design-education','','','2013-03-28 12:40:59','2013-03-28 12:40:59','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=759',0,'post','',0),
(779,7,'2011-06-01 19:08:11','2011-06-01 17:08:11','During one of the lectures of the RSFF course at the University of Twente, the Raw SoundScapers gave a live performance creating a marvelous intuitive soundscape for the film Powaqqatsi. The topic during this lecture was Mediation, ReMediation and HyperMediation, so the original music by Philip Glass was muted and replaced with interactive mediated music and sounds.\n\nThe loosely fitted group of musicians consisted of Werner Helmich, Herman Weeda and Sefrijn Langen all members of the Rawshaping Society. The experience of film, sound and atmosphere  were really perceived as immersive and stimulating.\n\nFor a sneak preview, watch:\n\n[vimeo 24522072]','Raw SoundScapers performing LIVE 2011','','publish','open','open','','raw-soundscapers-performing-live','','','2011-06-01 19:08:11','2011-06-01 17:08:11','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=779',0,'post','',0),
(794,7,'2011-06-22 16:38:59','2011-06-22 14:38:59','On Saturday June 25th, 2011 we will bring the LFDS to market. Embedding Design In Life. This cultural art &amp; design event will take place in Breukelen (Brooklyn) and start at 11:00 AM. Location is a beautiful parc in the center of town named Boom&amp;Bosch.\r\n\r\nWe are very curious and interested to see how the general public will react to our Loosely Fitted Design Synthesizer. Everybody who wants to try is welcome to make iterations and familiarize him/herself with the hybrid design tool. As a token of appreciation we will print one iteration by choice on a postcard as a memorabilia.\r\n\r\nTo keep the marketing objectified we will not convey that we are researchers or rawshapers.','Market Research ','','publish','open','open','','market-research','','','2013-03-28 12:40:23','2013-03-28 12:40:23','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=794',0,'post','',0),
(804,7,'2011-08-31 15:02:56','2011-08-31 13:02:56','During the Cultural Art &amp; Design Event in Breukelen in June 2011 (Brooklyn) the LFDS workbench attracted people from all walks of life. The two-handed interaction and manipulation of raw materials to create virtual abstract representations on screen were executed by children, adults, elderly and physically challenged people. The results derived from these interactions were really interesting and showed that the LFDS has a very low threshold for first time users. The experience to work with novice public volunteers was really awesome.\n\nThe reactions to the LFDS were enthusiastic and the tool was welcomed as an easy-to-use and user-friendly \'machine\'. The introduction to the  workbench, physical- and virtual interface received numerous spontaneous and cheerful reactions.\n\nThe results of the interactions were printed and handed to the participant as a token of appreciation for their creative and intuitive interactions. A Big Thanks to all the participants!\n\nSee the photos for more visual clues, enjoy!\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011592.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011596.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011598.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011600.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011604.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011607.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011614.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011616.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011617.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/25062011624.jpg\" /> <img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/20