(1417,7,'2013-03-23 16:01:03','2013-03-23 16:01:03','During one of the lectures of the RSFF course at the University of Twente, the Raw SoundScapers gave a live performance creating a marvelous intuitive soundscape for the film Powaqqatsi. The topic during this lecture was Mediation, ReMediation and HyperMediation, so the original music by Philip Glass was muted and replaced with interactive mediated music and sounds.\n\nThe loosely fitted group of musicians consisted of Werner Helmich, Herman Weeda and Sefrijn Langen all members of the Rawshaping Society. The experience of film, sound and atmosphere  were really perceived as immersive and stimulating.\n\nFor a sneak preview, watch:\n\n[vimeo 24522072]','Raw SoundScapers performing LIVE 2011','','inherit','open','open','','779-autosave','','','2013-03-23 16:01:03','2013-03-23 16:01:03','',779,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1417',0,'revision','',0),
