(1438,7,'2013-03-28 12:44:04','2013-03-28 12:44:04','On November 5th last, Raw Shaping participated in a Custom Value Engineering (CVE) session at ProRail in Utrecht, the Netherlands. The case at hand named \'Project Alkmaar\'  was organized in conjunction with stakeholders of ProRail, Dutch National Railways, City Council of Alkmaar, and Movares. The project entailed the decision process development on basis of different project parts and value engineering issues at stake. Raw Shaping introduced the Loosely Fitted Design Sythesizer [LFDS] as a Design Tool for collaborative interaction during this CVE session. The various actors [stakeholders] played an important role in testing and working with the intuitive design tool, firstly in trying to adapt to the new tool procedures and directly implementing these actions with face-to-face and two-handed interaction between them. Secondly, capturing decision instances during the  interactions making use and benefit from the intrinsic system choice-architecture. The initial set-up contained two LFDS workbenches on which two groups of stakeholders worked simultaneously, after we configured the set-up to one larger workbench allowing the group of nine (9) actors to collaborate together on the various issues at hand. An engineer of ProRail, specialized in VE, mediated and facilitated between the different project partners and enhanced the interaction by stimulating the discussions, bringing content to the design table and bridging the variety of project tasks with lively comments and possible solutions. The procedures took several hours of thinking-on-their-feet, knowing-in-action while consistently working through all the design constraints, discovering the ambiguity in possible solutions, making of abstract conceptualizations and tangible representations. In conclusion the outcome and results from this CVE session were captured in virtual instances and ordered in decision stacks, showing the variety in solutions and trade-offs. Following you will find some images and videos of the CVE session;\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05112010013.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05112010018.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05112010005.jpg\" /><img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/05112010010.jpg\" />\n\n[vimeo 16997579] [vimeo 16998789] [vimeo 16998018] [vimeo 17004503] [vimeo 17005888]','Raw Shaping + ProRail 2010','','inherit','open','open','','609-autosave','','','2013-03-28 12:44:04','2013-03-28 12:44:04','',609,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1438',0,'revision','',0),
