(1440,7,'2013-03-28 12:44:24','2013-03-28 12:44:24','Here you can find more information on RSFF [rawshaping formfinding] assignments and student work second year Bachelor industrial design engineering education at the University of Twente in the Netherlands. The RSFF course is loosely structured on intuitive design, collaborative interaction, hybridization of design tools and choice-architecture of which all components are intwined and afford the potential ramifications of our choices and interventions in design ideation and conceptualization. Furthermore the RSFF course incorporates and focuses on theories, mediation, techniques, technical philosophy, and practices of hybrid design processing. RSFF is not constrained by the traditional boundaries of design, engineering and planning. The emphasis of RSFF is on multi-disciplinary collaborative interaction and the role ambiguity, chaos and unpredictability play in designing and design processing during ideation and abstract conceptualization.\n\nStudent contributions by: Liesbeth Stam, Ani Hovhannisjan, Leon Spikker, Wessel de Vries, José Boekema, Liza Boon, Jorn van Manen, Marleen Offringa, Simon Hollander, Sabine Mooij, Jeanine van der Hoek, Mike Broekman, Gilbert van Veldhuizen, Charlot Boelens, Titia Lelie, ...\n\n<strong>Assignment RSFF I</strong> shown here is based on intuitive two-handed tangible interaction with physical tools and materials leading to thinking-on-your-feet, knowing-in-action and reflection-on-action. The rigour versus relevance theorem bringing about the fuzzy-logic as a loosely fittted organizational technique for developing intelligent, flexible and adaptive shapes, objects and forms. Gestural and manipulation activity are manifestations of design intent evoking emerging possibilities of new abstractions and creative solutions to support creativity and ideation. In this assignment the real and the virtual are merged by shifting from traditional analogue physical representations to digital virtual artifacts. This co-localization supported by real-world models (role model) from physical manipulation and 3d-scanning of these free-forms stimulate the hybridization of the real and the virtual realms. Underlying aspect of this assignment is the cognitive charge ignited through skill, intuition and sensory stimulation.\n\n<img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF01-4a.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF01-5.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF01-6.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF01-7.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF01-8.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF01-1.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF01-2.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF01-3.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF01-2.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF01-3.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF01-4.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0174742_Spikker_Leon_rsff01%20-%20Copy-1.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0174742_Spikker_Leon_rsff01%20-%20Copy-2.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/1