013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0201685_Manen_van_Jorn_RSFF01-6.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-2.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-3.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-4.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-5.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-6.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-7.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__I_s0215856_OffringaOpdracht_I-8.jpg\" /> [vimeo 15628496] [vimeo 15628653]\n\n<strong>Assignment RSFF II</strong> deals with lightweight design, mobility and spheres within nomadic cultures and organizational ephemeral structures. The emphasis is on sketching, ideation and three dimensional modeling of spatial solutions to create insight and understanding in spatial relationships, scalability and proportions. Unleashing the power of imagination by direct two-handed manipulation of tangible materials while stimulating observation, mediation and conceptualization. Design as an extension of Nature, the love of Nature and mimicking the serendipitous qualities of Nature encompass this assignment, supporting the need to embed and fit design in life as part of Nature. Loosely based on Sloterdijk\'s philosophy on Spheres about spaces of coexistence and the exploration of spheres in support of design thinking, communication and understanding of human behavior, mediation and manifestations of being. The nomadic aspects, globalization, lightweightness and creation of living spaces (spheres) are important aspects of this rawshaping design assignment.\n\n<img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-2.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-3.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-4.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-5.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-6.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-7.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-8.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0093025_Stam_Liesbeth_RSFF02-9.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0165425_Hollander_Simon_RSFF02.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF02-2.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF02-3.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF02-4.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF__II_s0171751_Hovhannisjan_Ani_RSFF02-5.jpg\" /> [vimeo 15628709] [vimeo 15630753]\n\n<strong>Assignment RSFF III</strong> is based on the double pendulum which undergoes and shows chaotic motion under initial conditions until it collapses. To track and visualize the chaotic motions LED lights are added to the limbs. The design and construction of the double pendulums are based on cheap and off-the-shelves components and materials to stimulate design students to make physical models and prototypes of their ideas and fuzzy notions. A variety of contraptions have been executed and fabricated on-the-fly, where loosely-fitted components become simple physical systems which can exhibit chaotic behavior. The results are shown in the images and videos in a wide variety of double pendulum visualizations.\n\n<img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0165425_Hollander_Simon_RSFF03.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0171751_Hovhannisian_Ani_RSFF03-2a.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0171751_Hovhannisian_Ani_RSFF03-3b.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0171751_Hovhannisian_Ani_RSFF03-4.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-1.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-10.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-11.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-12.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-13.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-3.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-4.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-5.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s0200212_Boon_Liza_RSFF_03-6.jpg\" /> <img src=\"_10 http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/10/RSFF_III_s020021