(1442,7,'2013-03-28 12:44:36','2013-03-28 12:44:36','RSFF is aiming at the identification of essential voids in the support of design processes offered by commonly available methods and tools. Some remarkable results were obtained during design sessions with novices and experts by engaging them in tangible experiments that were designed to stimulate and enhance their skills, tacit knowing and creativity that enable them to represent their ideas and concepts in an intuitive way. We explored and captured the differences in designer\'s behavior during use of \"analogue\" and digital representation tools. This approach leads us in the direction of creating an exciting hybrid design tool to bring the tacit and tangible elements of design back into CAD systems.\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/chart-xd.jpg\" />\n\n<img src=\" http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/RSFF%20schema%20sequences.png]','RSFF Framework','','inherit','open','open','','268-autosave','','','2013-03-28 12:44:36','2013-03-28 12:44:36','',268,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1442',0,'revision','',0),
(1443,7,'2013-03-28 12:44:42','2013-03-28 12:44:42','Raw Shaping Form Finding [RSFF] in Industrial Design Engineering education at the University of Twente in the Netherlands. Second year Bachelor students follow this course in \'finding form through intuitive raw shaping\'. The hybrid design tools [RSFF &amp; LFDS] we have developed during our [re]search, trials and explorations to bridge the gap between physical and virtual design creation processing are partly based on the findings and results derived from experimentations and assignments in conjunction with participating of students. RSFF just recently [2008] became part of the curriculum of IDE on the Education Sub-post (double-click on Education) you will find some interesting outcome of student design interaction.\n\nThe hugely untapped potential of igniting raw ideas, fuzzy notions and unpredictability in shape and form triggered by stimulating intuitive physical interaction based on loosely-fitted organizational techniques has lead us to RSFF.  To create and evoke design content through distributed cognition and randomly creative tinkering in combination with tangible materials and making of physical prototypes [product, service, system or other artifact] while simultaneously making use of real world and virtual reality tools enhances the design creation processing effectively.  With the RSFF approach we support the development of curiosity,  skill, talent, creativity and serendipity by immersing students in cognitive stimulation during design processing that simultaneously enhances their perception and abstract representation. The creation and embedding of aesthetic qualities, imagination, awareness and engagement within design education is pivotal to understand your role as a designer not only as part of the product creation process, but more importantly as part of your vision, responsibility and purpose as a designer towards the often transient Design Industry. Understanding, adding perspective and being knowledgeable on the enduring globalization and manufacturing of consent on topics like sustainability,  eco-efficiency (C2C) and bioenvironmental issues are integrate part and fundamental to design education.\n\nSketching, doodling, drawing, sculpting, modeling and tinkering with two-hands making things will bring out a variety in possible solutions and a richness and diversity in ideas and abstractions. RSFF is about taking your time to think-on-your-feet, evolve your physical actions and colligate your creative sparks leading to improvisation and innovation on-the-fly. Bestowing meaning and passing of judgement are often misleading and disruptive in design processing, RSFF stimulates choice-options and advocates reprieve of opinion while design processing leaving the window of opportunity open to allow accidental discoveries and stimulation of creativity. Choice-architecture in most design strategies often leads to linear processing and results thereof, in RSFF we allow and afford random processing making numerous iterations incorporating and entailing a World of Ideas.','RSFF Education','','inherit','open','open','','413-autosave','','','2013-03-28 12:44:42','2013-03-28 12:44:42','',413,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1443',0,'revision','',0),
