(1595,7,'2014-03-26 13:17:05','2014-03-26 13:17:05','The <strong>ASME 2014 International Design and Engineering Technical Conferences &amp; Computers and Information in Engineering Conference (IDETC/CIE 2014)</strong> will take place during <strong>August 17-20, 2014</strong> in Buffalo, NY, USA.\r\n\r\nFpr more information: <a href=\"http://www.asmeconferences.org/IDETC2014/index.cfm\">http://www.asmeconferences.org/IDETC2014/index.cfm</a>\r\n\r\nRST will present the following papers:\r\n\r\nMIXED REALITY TOOLS FOR PLAYFUL REPRESENTATION OF IDEATION,\r\nCONCEPTUAL BLENDING AND PASTICHE IN DESIGN AND ENGINEERING\r\n\r\nand:\r\n\r\nINNOVATIVE TOOL FOR SPECIFYING CUSTOMER REQUIREMENTS\r\n\r\nVES: Game Eco-Systems in Engineering:\r\n\r\nThe following list details the breakdown of themes that would include the above mentioned topics. The Track envisages as a starting compendium for serious gaming concepts that make up a game ecosystem for engineering. Knowledge discovery in SG-VES: a human-centered approach - Knowledge acquisition by user experience - Serious games and emotional interaction in learning and transfer of knowledge - Study on pervasive systems and gameplay experiences - Mapping of learning goals to (serious) game mechanics Software architecture and design - Game and game engine architecture - Game design in theory and practice Feedback and game/learning mechanics for engineering physics (includes human-computer interaction, game engines, analytics and assessment frameworks, game authoring, asset creation and management, etc.) - Human Interface Devices SG-VES Applications - Applied and research platforms for engineering physics - Big Data/ Data Exploration in High Value Manufacturing/Engineering Sectors, Space Applications and the Physical Sciences, Creative Industries - Product design and manufacturing: modeling, authoring, control and concurrent workspaces (includes haptic-VR techniques, pervasive techniques and social networks, life cycle management, etc.) - Transportation engineering: modeling (includes driving simulation and traffic modeling) - Medical and clinical: Surgical training, sensorimotor rehabilitation, etc. - Robotics: Simulation and Emulation; Design; Evaluation; Deployment; Control Cyber-physical systems - Mechanistic / Humanistic / Biomimetic approaches - Body Area Networks for VES (live role play problem solving; run-time authoring and telefeedback controls) - Ubiquitous human-driven interfaces for creativity, tinkering and ideation - Multi-sensory interaction in games dedicated to engineering design - Multimodal data capture and process modeling of game mechanics/dynamics and learning mechanisms Transdisciplinarity and interdisciplinarity in SG-VES - Reuse of virtual assets and knowledge transfer (e.g. reusable design patterns) - Specifications, standards, interoperability - Intuitive design tools in playful (SG) stochastic CAD-yards (beyond the sandbox) - Epigenetic mechanisms in design and engineering systems (stressors/ environment/ imprinting) - Epistemic, semiotic and ergotic requirements for SG-VES - Heuristic shape ideation, polysemy and pastiche for Design &amp; Engineering and VES. Game Ecosystems for creativity, design and innovation - Frameworks and perspectives for Game-based VES - Game-enhanced creativity - Synthetic reflective pools for imagination, stimulation and interpretation - Cultural and contextual hybrid synthetic environments forD&amp;E in VES - Game ecosystems for engineering design and innovation - Emergent gaming technologies for SG-VES (democratization; low cost)','ASME IDETC/CIE 2014','','inherit','open','open','','1562-revision-6','','','2014-03-26 13:17:05','2014-03-26 13:17:05','',1562,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1595',0,'revision','',0),
