(1712,7,'2015-06-24 14:49:54','2015-06-24 14:49:54','[caption id=\"attachment_1693\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1072\"]<a href=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/IMG_20150618_142426711_HDR-e1435156658836.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1693\" alt=\"3-D VoxMod_RST 2015\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/IMG_20150618_142426711_HDR-e1435156658836.jpg\" width=\"1072\" height=\"602\" /></a> 3-D VoxMod_RST 2015[/caption]\r\n\r\nA fast, simple and easy to use 3-D Voxel Modeler (click on photo for full scene) to \'scan\' your physical models or tangible objects and create virtual models for further iteration, exploration and/or transformation. The hybrid tool is partly based on the Shape-from-Silhouette (SFS) principle and work done by Keith Forbes (2009) on algorithms for processing in MATLAB. The device consists of two mirrors and a HD-video camera to capture shape-silhouettes and create a Visual Hull as a virtual representation of the real object/model. The working prototype is designed and build by Arno van Dijk (Ba-assignment RST) as part of the Rawshaping Technology project at the University of Twente in the Netherlands.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1697\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"800\"]<a href=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/IMG_20150618_141352525_HDR-e1435157153451.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1697\" alt=\"Arno with 3-DVoxMod\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/IMG_20150618_141352525_HDR-e1435157153451.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" /></a> Arno with 3-DVoxMod[/caption]\r\n\r\nClick on photo for full Arno','3-D Voxel Modeler by Rawshaping Technology','','inherit','open','closed','','1692-revision-7','','','2015-06-24 14:49:54','2015-06-24 14:49:54','',1692,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1712',0,'revision','',0),
