(1729,7,'2015-07-02 10:04:33','2015-07-02 10:04:33','<div>\r\n<div data-expand-tooltip=\"Click to expand description\">\r\n\r\n\"Thirteen year old Larissa came to play and interact with the hybrid design tool, NXt-LFDS, in our laboratory at the University of Twente to explore the possibilities. She had no previous experience with the tool but that did not matter, after some hints and clues she performed wonderfully. She showed motivation, happiness and enjoyment during the interaction, thereby creating many iterations one after the other. No hang-ups or boundaries that constraint her creative abilities and process. Larissa was dancing and playing her way through an hour long process of exploration, transformation, and translation switching between real and virtual content. She was determined and committed to keep the flow of ideas and imagination constant and fluid, subsequently generating rich virtual content driven by intuitive common sense. Child\'s play!\"\r\n\r\n\'Man is most nearly himself when he achieves the seriousness of a child at play.\' - Heraclitus\"\r\n\r\nFor video please click link:<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/132374254\"> https://vimeo.com/132374254</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','NXt-LFDS & Larissa - 2015 _Hybrid Design Tool, Creative Processing and Spontaneity','','publish','open','closed','','nxt-lfds-larissa-2015-_hybrid-design-tool-creative-processing-and-spontaneity','','','2015-07-02 10:05:35','2015-07-02 10:05:35','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1729',0,'post','',0),
