(1795,7,'2015-11-04 12:06:54','2015-11-04 12:06:54','<a href=\"https://lifeatnedap.com/agenda/nedap-talks-user-experience-is-simpler-better/\">https://lifeatnedap.com/agenda/nedap-talks-user-experience-is-simpler-better/</a>\r\n<h1>User eXperience: Is simpler better?</h1>\r\n<div>De Grote Kerk, Enschede</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nWe all want applications and devices to be easy to use. Often that means they provide a pleasant user experience, and that you can achieve your goal effectively. The operation of complicated applications and devices is becoming more accessible by the day. But: in what way does this changes us in terms of who we are and how we evolve as humans? Does taking away complexity influence our learning capacities? And how does this has an effect on us at a social, pedagogic and ethical level not only for an individual, but for us as a society?\r\n\r\nThis session of Nedap Talks will be held at De Grote Kerk in Enschede, on November 4th, 7:30PM. The topic is User eXperience (UX) design, and more specifically how it affects us socially, pedagogically and ethically.\r\n\r\n===============Wendrich postulates:\r\n\r\nWith the introduction of digital solutions (i.e. ICT) and the revolution in personal wearable computer systems and access to digital services (i.e. smartphones, tablets etc.) the simplicity and affordance for built-in functionalities within these apparatuses illustrates the higher-complexity that allows for seemingly fluid interactions with these apparently ‘simple’ solutions, modalities, and functions. Even here we witness the relative ease in uptake and usage by propagated users, whereby the play, swipe, and interaction with ‘illusionary’ icons and widgets (IxD) supposedly triggers the user into an immersive experience of function, interaction, and expectation in action-solution-gratification. The interactive relationship UX with digital tools and multi-modalities, facilitated through the UI and GUI, suggests effortless support and assistance of the user in their direct (real-time) needs and wishes for particular gratification (instant) and solution-fit-for-purpose.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','RST @ Nedap Talks on November 4th, 2015','','inherit','open','closed','','1790-revision-2','','','2015-11-04 12:06:54','2015-11-04 12:06:54','',1790,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1795',0,'revision','',0),
