(1830,7,'2016-06-13 17:12:19','2016-06-13 17:12:19','August, 21 - 24, 2016 - Charlotte, North-Carolina, USA\r\n\r\nRST will present three papers and host a symposium/panel sesion during the conference. Papers are titled:\r\n\r\n- AIRFLOW INTERACTION INTERFACE: Playful 3-D CAD and gaming\r\n\r\n- Hybrid Design Tools in a Social Virtual Reality Using Networked Oculus Rift: A Feasibility Study in Remote Real-time Interaction [co-authored with University of Washington, New Parsons School of Design, NY, Effat University]\r\n\r\n- Framework and Feasibility Study for Pairwise Comparison of Customer Requirements Tool (CRT) [co-authored with Tampere University of Technology &amp; University of Tampere, Finland]\r\n\r\nThe range of functions of products mechanical engineering and related domains increases constantly. This complicates the product development process due to an escalating number of components, the interactions among these components as well as by a growing number of involved team members. Virtual environments and systems offer an opportunity to cope with these challenges. Virtual environments are computer-generated immersive 3D worlds that facilitate to experience the design of virtual product. Systems for virtual environments encompass all hardware (interaction devices, system architectures, projection systems) and software (rendering methods, data management), which is required to deploy this type of virtual environments. The symposium of virtual environments and systems is a platform to introduce and discuss the latest advances of virtual environment and systems for mechanical engineering and related domains. We invite authors to submit original articles including the topics (but not limited): -Advanced rendering and Computer Graphics Techniques, Computer Vision Algorithm, Advanced Display Technology, Emerging Technologies, Tracking and Sensing, and Softwarization &amp; Big Shift.\r\n\r\nFor more information: <a href=\"https://www.asme.org/events/idetccie\">https://www.asme.org/events/idetccie</a>\r\n\r\nTracks: <a href=\"https://www.asme.org/events/idetccie/program#/track/detail/2\">https://www.asme.org/events/idetccie/program#/track/detail/2</a>','RST @ ASME IDETC CIE 2016','','publish','open','closed','','rst-idetc-cie-2016','','','2016-06-13 17:21:33','2016-06-13 17:21:33','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1830',0,'post','',0),
