strial applications. Furthermore, companies are investing billions into making immersive virtual worlds and augmented reality widely available to mainstream public in mass quantities (i.e., especially for “gamer” consumers but also a wide range of other applications). We have also seen a trend in customization. Nowadays, thanks to the availability of 3-D printing technologies as well as open-source electronic prototyping platform, custom interfaces can be easily designed. We have observed a shift of interest from Virtual Environment to Mixed ones, sometimes called Augmented, sometimes named \"Blended\". Furthermore as the number of applications increases, new challenges are presented to the scientific community. This purpose of this VES panel is to encourage discussion and exchange of views about current and new trends for Virtual and Immersive/Blended Systems and the transference of knowledge over multiple domains.\r\n\r\n<strong>VES SYMPOSIUMS:</strong>\r\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>CIE-21 Virtual Environments and Systems (VES)</strong> <em> (Symposium)</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">Symposium Organizer: Robert E. Wendrich, <em>IDE at University of Twente</em>\r\nLocation: Enschede , Netherlands\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:info@rawshaping.com\">info@rawshaping.com</a>Symposium Co-Organizer: Pramita Mitra, <em>Ford Motor Company</em>\r\nLocation: Bloomfield Township , MI , United States\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:pmitra3@ford.com\">pmitra3@ford.com</a>\r\n\r\nSymposium Co-Organizer: Theo Lim, <em>Heriot-watt Univ</em>\r\nLocation: Edinburgh , Scotland\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:t.lim@hw.ac.uk\">t.lim@hw.ac.uk</a>\r\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>CIE-22 VES: Technology and Applications (TA)</strong> <em> (Symposium)</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">Symposium Organizer: Robert E. We