(1925,7,'2017-06-27 16:22:37','2017-06-27 16:22:37','RST @ VRPT 2017\r\n\r\n@rawshapingtech\r\n\r\nFor more information: <a href=\"http://www.kaemart.it/2017summerschool/\">http://www.kaemart.it/2017summerschool/</a>\r\n\r\nVirtual and Physical Prototyping is recognized as a practice useful for the reduction of the development costs of industrial products. Such prototypes are anticipation of a product shape-function that does not exist in reality yet, but that appears and behaves as it were real. Therefore, a Virtual and Physical Prototype simulates how a product looks like and how it works, and can be used to test how users use and interact with it, etc.\r\nVirtual and Physical Prototypes can be multisensory and multimodal. Research outcomes of recent years and the enormous improvements in price and performances in ICT technology have enabled the realization of complex prototypes integrating real-time, immersive, mixed or augmented, visual interaction, as well as haptic, sonic and olfactory interaction.\r\n\r\nCreating effective Virtual Prototypes requires interdisciplinary skills, which go beyond engineering and IT disciplines, and include crucial disciplines related to human aspects such as human factors, human perception, etc.\r\n<pre>The School will host seminar talks given by international researchers, \r\nexperts in various IT and human-related disciplines to use in \r\nVirtual and Physical Prototyping.</pre>\r\n<pre>List of lecturers:</pre>\r\nMonica Bordegoni (Politecnico di Milano) – Introduction, Olfactory Interfaces\r\n\r\nFrancesco Ferrise (Politecnico di Milano) – Introduction, Multisensory interaction design\r\n\r\nAlberto Gallace (Università di Milano Bicocca) – Multisensory perception\r\n\r\nVincent Hayward (ISIR – Paris, France) – Haptic/Tactile Technology\r\n\r\nStefania Serafin (Aalborg University Copenhagen) – Sonic interaction design\r\n\r\nRobert Wendrich (University of Twente, the Netherlands) – Experience design\r\n\r\nAlba Cappellieri (Politecnico di Milano) - Fashion Tech\r\n\r\nSatwik Saraswat (Adidas, Germany) – Case study\r\n<em>\r\n</em>','Virtual and Physical Prototyping 2017 Summerschool - Politecnico di Milano 10-14 July','','publish','open','closed','','virtual-and-physical-prototyping-2017-virtual-prototyping-ss-politecnico-di-milano-10-14-july','','','2017-08-06 16:06:39','2017-08-06 16:06:39','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1925',0,'post','',0),
