(2054,7,'2019-03-21 11:11:01','2019-03-21 11:11:01','<h3>Hybrid design tools for individual and collaborative interaction based on creativity, applied innovation and mixed reality.</h3>\r\nManipulation of tangible physical objects, tools and materials in a synthetic and natural-physical environments. Bi-manual interaction in sensorial space supported by virtual design tools. The hybrid design tool stores the captured iterations as polygon meshes (listing) by mimicking the tangible representations, and storing them in a database as time-stamped snapshots. By creating such a timeline of the evolving tangible object manipulations captured by means of a vision system, the hybrid tool allows the fusion of different polygon meshes with subsequent optimization (synthesis).\r\n\r\nExploration through variety, ambiguity and spontaneity we foster non-linear, non-regular thinking and doing. Thereby evoking insight, enhance understanding and create enjoyment during interaction, decision-making and problem-solving.\r\n\r\nExperimentation Haptic and vision-based representation configurations for testing and experimental purposes. The aim of the experimentation is to measure, explore and quantify the effectiveness of un-tethered and tethered tool use, apparent routines, mediation of restraints, signs of flow and stall, manual dexterity as well as gestural and skill development.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-2068 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Tosca-I-logo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"210\" height=\"95\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2059 \" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/01-TOSCA-I-PLATE.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"698\" height=\"331\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2061 \" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/02-TOSCA-I-BOWL.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"698\" height=\"390\" />\r\n<h3><img class=\"wp-image-2069 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploa