(2102,7,'2019-05-17 09:56:39','2019-05-17 09:56:39','<div class=\"date-loc-wrapper hni-grid\" data-min-height=\"2\">\r\n<h2 class=\"subtitle h4\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>  </strong><strong>HYBRID DESIGN TOOL </strong>by Rawshaping Technology (RST-HDT)</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class=\"subtitle h4\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>19/05/2019 – 15/09/2019</strong></h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">In close cooperation with Het Nieuwe Instituut: <a href=\"https://neuhaus.hetnieuweinstituut.nl/\">https://neuhaus.hetnieuweinstituut.nl/</a>,WDKA: <a href=\"https://www.wdka.nl/research/neulab-different-learning-environment\">https://www.wdka.nl/research/neulab-different-learning-environment</a>, Werner Helmich from Frontwise Digital Innovators: <a href=\"https://frontwise.com/\">https://frontwise.com/</a> and Olaf Grevenstuk from Disini, Rawshaping Technology (RST) will present their hybrid design tool: a Loosely Fitted Design Synthesizer (LFDS) during the four month Neuhaus|Neulab event at Het Nieuwe Instituut in Rotterdam.</h3>\r\nhttps://vimeo.com/336774745\r\n<h2 class=\"subtitle h4\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-2090 \" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_20190515_194654857_HDR-e1558085022331.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"321\" /></strong></h2>\r\nThe RST-HDT_LFDS could be  summarized as follows:\r\n\r\nThe design ideation process is about making abstract representations often based on fuzzy notions, ideas or prerequisite requirements with the use of various design tools. We introduce an interactive hybrid design tool (HDT) to assist and support singular design activity or multiple collaborative creative processing, product creation, analogue/digital ways-of-working and tinkering. The HDT enables the designer or design team to work smoothly with tangible artifacts, physical objects and traditional design tools. It enables them to freely and intuitively manipulate these ob