(2171,7,'2020-03-12 12:01:37','2020-03-12 12:01:37','RSTs contribution is titled: CREATIVE THINKING: COMPUTATIONAL TOOLS IMBUED WITH AI\r\n\r\nThis paper presents a test bed for AI technology on the integration of creative AI (CAI) with hybrid design tools (HDTs). The objective is to build and develop tools and programs for creative people (e.g. designers, engineers) to use, whereby the artificial intelligence (AI) software acts as a creative collaborator rather than a mere tool. The goal is to find a set of guiding principles, metaphors and ideas that inform the development of a CAI praxis imbued with computational support tools, new theories, experiments, and applications. Results and findings are presented of early-stage research.\r\n\r\nKEYWORDS:\r\nartificial intelligence (AI), design creativity, design tools, cyber physical systems\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-2169 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/2015-10-25_14-00-17_136-350x350.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"223\" height=\"223\" /> <img class=\"wp-image-2170 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/20180718_154139_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"348\" height=\"231\" />\r\n\r\nSpecial thanks to Max Meijer for his contribution.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','RST@DESIGN2020','','inherit','closed','closed','','2165-revision-v1','','','2020-03-12 12:01:37','2020-03-12 12:01:37','',2165,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=2171',0,'revision','',0),
