e from a process of cultural bricolage that leads to cultural métissage and therefore hybridity and heterogeneity. To understand the power of a dialectical concept of diaspora, we begin by articulating what is used as the tacit norm, the idea of an entity being identical with itself—selfsame identity—and contrast it with cultural (dialectical, postmodern) perspectives that are founded on plural singularity, difference, and non-identical repetition (Deleuze 1968/1994).\r\n\r\nApplication, relevance , exploration, and integration of people, technology and society (?) / ecology(?) &gt; experience design as a foundational layer of investigation and exploration for cyber-physical systems (CPS) &gt; the interactive modalities, multiple modalities, multi-sensorial possibilities facilitated with interactive possibilities (human-machine spectrum) meta-cognitive, haptic-tactile expierences in connection with devices, platforms, machines, systems.\r\n\r\nTrade-off and approximation between research and practition &gt; another hybridity\r\n\r\nRandom atoms (material properties change over time, transformative qualities, features, functionalities).\r\n\r\nThe human and the machine were hybridized as parts of a larger \"synchronous organism\". \"Automation\r\nis not an extension of the mechanical principles of fragmentation and separation of operations. It is rather the invasion of the mechanical world by the instantaneous character of electricity. That is why those involved in automation insist that it is a way of thinking, as much as it is a way of doing.\" (Huhtamo, 1999)\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1994 size-large\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/bridge-what-gap-450x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"169\" />\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">What gap do you wish to bridge, what bridge do you wish to gap?</p>\r\nHybrid learning (blended learning) in a design engineering context: a mixed method approach\r\nface-to-face + on-line to enhance and foster “the broad education necessary to understand the impact of industrial design engineering solutions in a global, economic, environmental, and societal context” (Wendrich, 2016)','RST Launches: HYBRIDITY XD - Blended Space + Learning Environment','','inherit','closed','closed','','1982-revision-v1','','','2018-03-22 21:29:36','2018-03-22 21:29:36','',1982,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=1999',0,'revision','',0),
