(2006,7,'2018-06-21 08:54:34','2018-06-21 08:54:34','<strong>THE DIGITAL FABRICATION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Department of Mechanical Engineering, Politecnico di Milano, 2-6 July 2018</strong>\r\n\r\nThe 9<sup>th</sup> edition of the Summer School will focus on the following topics:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Ideation of multisensory interfaces for innovative products</li>\r\n 	<li>Development of virtual and physical prototypes proofing the concepts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em>Virtual and Physical Prototyping</em> is recognized as a practice useful for the reduction of the development costs of industrial products. Such prototypes are anticipation of a product shape-function that does not exist in reality yet, but that appears and behaves as it were real. Therefore, a Virtual and Physical Prototype simulates how a product looks like and how it works, and can be used to test how users use and interact with it. Virtual and Physical Prototypes can be multisensory and multimodal. Research outcomes of recent years and the enormous improvements in price and performances in ICT technology have enabled the realization of complex prototypes integrating 3D acquisition and 3D printing, immersive, virtual, mixed or augmented reality, multisensory interaction, including haptic, sonic and olfactory interaction.\r\n\r\nThe School will host talks given by international researchers, experts in various IT and human-related disciplines to use in Virtual and Physical Prototyping.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monica Bordegoni </strong>(Politecnico di Milano, DMEC) – Introduction, Multisensory Technology\r\n\r\n<strong>Francesco Ferrise </strong>(Politecnico di Milano. DMEC) – Multisensory Technology\r\n\r\n<strong>Alberto Gallace </strong>(Università di Milano Bicocca) – Multisensory Perception and Design\r\n\r\n<strong>Robert Wendrich </strong>(University of Twente, the Netherlands) – Experience Design\r\n\r\n<strong>Sandro Barone / Armando Razionale</strong> (Università di Pisa) – 3D reconstruction, modeling and printing\r\n\r\n<strong>Marco Ajovalasit</strong> (Politecnico di Milano, Design) – Interaction Design\r\n\r\n<strong>Jouke Verlinden </strong>(Delft University) – Digital Fabrication\r\n\r\n<strong>Adidas Company </strong>(Design Center - Munich) – Case Study\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kaemart.it/2018summerschool\">http://www.kaemart.it/2018summerschool</a>','VRPT 2018 Summerschool Virtual Prototyping + Experience Design','','publish','open','closed','','vrpt-2018-summerschool-virtual-prototyping-experience-design','','','2018-06-21 11:30:29','2018-06-21 11:30:29','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=2006',0,'post','',0),
(2008,7,'2018-06-21 08:54:34','2018-06-21 08:54:34','<strong>THE DIGITAL FABRICATION</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Department of Mechanical Engineering, Politecnico di Milano, 2-6 July 2018</strong>\r\n\r\nThe 9<sup>th</sup> edition of the Summer School will focus on the following topics:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Ideation of multisensory interfaces for innovative products</li>\r\n 	<li>Development of virtual and physical prototypes proofing the concepts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em>Virtual and Physical Prototyping</em> is recognized as a practice useful for the reduction of the development costs of industrial products. Such prototypes are anticipation of a product shape-function that does not exist in reality yet, but that appears and behaves as it were real. Therefore, a Virtual and Physical Prototype simulates how a product looks like and how it works, and can be used to test how users use and interact with it. Virtual and Physical Prototypes can be multisensory and multimodal. Research outcomes of recent years and the enormous improvements in price and performances in ICT technology have enabled the realization of complex prototypes integrating 3D acquisition and 3D printing, immersive, virtual, mixed or augmented reality, multisensory interaction, including haptic, sonic and olfactory interaction.\r\n\r\nThe School will host talks given by international researchers, experts in various IT and human-related disciplines to use in Virtual and Physical Prototyping.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monica Bordegoni </strong>(Politecnico di Milano, DMEC) – Introduction, Multisensory Technology\r\n\r\n<strong>Francesco Ferrise </strong>(Politecnico di Milano. DMEC) – Multisensory Technology\r\n\r\n<strong>Alberto Gallace </strong>(Università di Milano Bicocca) – Multisensory Perception and Design\r\n\r\n<strong>Robert Wendrich </strong>(University of Twente, the Netherlands) – Experience Design\r\n\r\n<strong>Sandro Barone / Armando Razionale</strong> (Università di Pisa) – 3D reconstruction, modeling and printing\r\n\r\n<strong>Marco Ajovalasit</strong> (Politecnico di Milano, Design) – Interaction Design\r\n\r\n<strong>Jouke Verlinden </strong>(Delft University) – Digital Fabrication\r\n\r\n<strong>Adidas Company </strong>(Design Center - Munich) – Case Study','VRPT 2018 Summerschool Virtual Prototyping + Experience Design','','inherit','closed','closed','','2006-revision-v1','','','2018-06-21 08:54:34','2018-06-21 08:54:34','',2006,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=2008',0,'revision','',0),
(2009,7,'2018-06-21 09:11:33','2018-06-21 09:11:33','The <strong>ASME 2018 International Design Engineering Technical Conferences &amp; Computers and Information in Engineering Conference (IDETC/CIE 2018)</strong> will take place during <strong>August 26-29, 2018</strong> in Quebec City, Canada. IDETC/CIE 2018 will highlight emergent technologies that impact the critical engineering issues of product design and development, manufacturing, and the management and integration of information systems throughout the product life-cycle. These events are key international meetings for design and manufacturing engineers in academia, government and industry.\r\n\r\nRobert E. Wendrich is CIE-VES Symposium Chair and Organizer for this year\'s edition of the Conference.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.asmeconferences.org/IDETC2018/CallForPapersDetail.cfm\">http://www.asmeconferences.org/IDETC2018/CallForPapersDetail.cfm</a>\r\n\r\nRobert Wendrich of RST will present two papers on topic of Blended Spaces, Collaboration and Computer Supported Learning Tools and Sensoriums, Experiences Intertwined with Toolness and Tools for Conceptualization. Furthermore, he will be one of the speakers and panelist during  the CIE-22 VES Panel Session: \'Advancement and Enhanced Integration of Digital Technology Systems, VR Applications, CPS-Systems and Tools for Design Engineering.\' Robert will give a talk titled: <em>\'Realities Are Not What IT Seems; Illusions Mess with Our Minds.\'  </em><em>\r\n</em>\r\n\r\nIn addition, a special session has been organized (first time ever) in CIE-25-1: Video, Visualization and Virtual Demonstration of Prototypes and Simulations will be held during the days of the conference to allow participants to view, discuss, present and represent state-of-the-art and ongoing research endeavours and projects.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2013 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/LMDS_Capture_1506359091869-350x350.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2014 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.rawshaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/LMDS_Capture_1506359680758-350x350.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.asme.org/events/idetccie\">https://www.asme.org/events/idetccie</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','RST @ ASME IDETC CIE VES 2018 - Québéc City, QC, CDN','','publish','open','closed','','rst-asme-idetc-cie-ves-2018-quebec-city-qc-cdn','','','2018-06-21 11:15:24','2018-06-21 11:15:24','',0,'http://www.rawshaping.com/?p=2009',0,'post','',0),
